United Nations Secretary-General Antonio Guterres says the relationship between UN and South Africa remains solid as the country plays an important role in the continent. Guterres says South Africa plays a significant role towards peace and security processes in Africa. “The mediation in South Sudan and also in Burundi is a vital contribution by the South African government.” He added that South Africa is a very devoted country as it continues to shows its commitment to honour Human Rights regulations. Click video below for full interview with the United Nations Secretary-General Antonio Guterres: 